DOMMatrixPreMultiplySelf.summary: The preMultiplySelf() method of the interface modifies the matrix by pre-multiplying it with the specified DOMMatrix. This is equivalent to the dot product Bâ‹…A, where matrix A is the source matrix and B is the matrix given as an input to the method. If no matrix is specified as the multiplier, the matrix is multiplied by a matrix in which every element is 0 except the bottom-right corner and the element immediately above and to its left: m33 and m34. These have the default value of 1.
DOMMatrixPreMultiplySelf.returns: Returns itself; a DOMMatrix updated to results of the applied multiplications.
